title: Regulatory uncertainty as commercial human spaceflight takes off
summary: As two companies prepare to begin or resume commercial suborbital human spaceflights, they are facing uncertainty about how the safety of the people on those flights will be regulated.

title: Launch Roundup – Arianespace launching Ariane 5 final flight; SpaceX to fly one of last Starlink v1.5 flights
summary: Three launches are currently planned for the week of July 2 through July 9. The first one is on America’s birthday, Tuesday, July 4, but is a European rocket making its 117th and final flight. Later in the week, SpaceX plans two Falcon 9 flights with Starlink payloads on Friday, July 7 and Sunday, July 9. These flights will be the 98th, 99th, and 100th orbital launch attempts of 2023.

title: Vega C Return Delayed Following Static Fire Anomaly

title: NASA Orders More Solar Arrays For ISS
summary: NASA has now revealed its plans to enhance the station's capabilities even further. The space agency has partnered with Boeing and Redwire to add two additional solar arrays, known as ISS Roll-Out Solar Arrays (IROSA), to the ISS.
